pr_body: Adding Contributing guidelines, README files and other base repository setup files in Xwiki-aws repo.

pr_title: XAWS-2: Setting up XWiki CDK Base setup for Production installations
pr_body: The production installation CDK would give Cloudformation templates to spin up Clusters and RDS instances for setting up XWiki servers and database servers in a modular way.

pr_title: XAWS-3: Setting up base CDK setup for XWiki demo/testing installations
pr_body: This CDK code would be used for spinning up ec2 instances with bootstrapping scripts which can be later used to generate AMIs

pr_title: XAWS-4: Added CDK code for XWiki demo installation with unit tests.
pr_body: Added CDK code for installing XWiki demo using user-script on EC2 instance of type T2.medium inside public subnet of default VPC of the user's account. Added unit tests using jest test framework.

pr_title: XAWS-5: Added CDK code for configuring production XWiki with MySQL in AWS account
pr_body: Added code to configure stacks for provisioning VPC with four subnets, RDS using AWS Aurora, File-System using AWS EFS, and Application Loadbalancer. Details of the Architecture is explained [here](https://design.xwiki.org/xwiki/bin/view/Proposal/Elastic%20Compute%20Cloud-based%20Amazon%20Machine%20Image%20for%20XWiki/). Also added an easy-to-edit config file to change the XWiki version, AWS region, and account number.
